FuncDef: The display debugging mpls te command is used to view the MPLS debugging enabled by the debugging mpls te command.
Examples: TE_MANAGEMENT events debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT error debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT timer debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT fsm debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT delete debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT update debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT create debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT gmpls debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT reoptimization debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT auto-bandwidth debugging switch is on
TE_MANAGEMENT frr debugging switch is on
TE_AGENT error debugging switch is on
TE_AGENT timer debugging switch is on
TE_AGENT fsm debugging switch is on
TE_AGENT tunnel debugging switch is on
TE_AGENT lsp debugging switch is on
TE_AGENT events debugging switch is on
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
Run the display debugging mpls te command to check the mpls debugging.
Check whether the mpls debugging switch set by the debugging mpls te command is enabled.
